Description: Roosevelt aims to be a web application development framework based on Express. Roosevelt intends to abstract all boilerplates necessary to build a typical Express app and provide a uniform MVC structure for application development.
Twee.io is a Node.js framework that offers developers conventions that will protect OOP and MVC maneer code from issues that arise in big projects and applications.

Framework Name: Grasshopper Node.js Framework by Chandra Sekar S
Description: Grasshopper is a Node.js framework that offers web application development support. The framework provides features such as integrated support for dependency injection, filter for intercepting requests, supports basic and digest authentication, and the compression of static files.

Framework Name: Spine JavaScript Framework by Spine JS Project
Description: Spine is a lightweight MVC library for building JavaScript web applications. It intends to offer developers structure and an architecture that complements patterns such as de-coupled components and CommonJS modules to help with code quality and maintainability. The framework's library is written in CoffeeScript.

rAppid.js intends to offer developers a declarative javascript web application framework for rapid web application development. It allows for the use of XML to define the structure of the application and to configure components such as datasources or routes. The framework aims to work by allowing the XML (XAML) to be translated to javascript components during runtime to render itself as HTML5 DOM elements. The framework was initally designed as a pure client side javascript library, however, it now offers an expendable web server with a request pipeline and different request handlers.

Framework Name: Josi Node.js Framework by Matt Lee
Description: Josi is a web framework for node.js that aims to be a MVC web framework (e.g. ASP.NET MVC, Rails, Django). It allows for common features with Node.js, such as its asynchronous, event driven nature, possible to utilitze.

Framework Name: Raddish Node.js Framework by Jasper van Rijbroek
Description: Raddish is an open-source NodeJS Framework that aims to provide a framework for modern web applications. The framework aims to be a design pattern based architecure that gives developers more flexibility in application development and features. It allows for what is written to be resuable and extensible pieces of code.

Framework Name: Code Kart Node.js Framework by Yangjie Pro
Description: Codekart is a Node.js framework that intends to havea very small footprint, built for Node.js developers who need a simple toolkit to create full-featured web applications. The framework allows for developers to use shared hosting accounts and clients with deadlines.

Framework Name: Locomotive Node.js Framework by Jared Hanson
Description: Locomotive is a framework that aims to bring structure and MVC patterns to web applications using Node and Express.

Framework Name: Trintejs Node.js Framework by Alexey Gordeyev
Description: Trintejs is a MVC boilerplate framework for ExpressJS backed by CaminteJS and Bootstrap.

Framework Name: Agni Node.js Framework by Lorenzo Tabacchini
Description: Agni is a web framework built on top of Express, based on the principle of convention over configuration. It intends to allow for a thin layer of abstraction for route definition and directory organization, without giving up the full power and flexibility of Express. The framework does not include any database abstraction system, but leaves this choice to the developer.

Framework Name: Sleekjs Node.js Framework by Cubet Techno Labs
Description: Sleek.js is an MVC Wrapper Framework implemented from Node.jS that aims to be built-in with base dependency on handlebars.js. The Sleek.js architecture allows developers to follow the common format of MVC to handle and build sites with pluggable modules & themes support.
Geddy is a Node.js framework that aims to provide a structured web framework for web development.

Compoundjs is a MVC framework that aims to work on servers and browsers to build web applications to provide well-organized interfaces for Express compatible applications. The framework is a compound of three things: the Express framework, structure, and extensions.

Framework Name: Strapi Node.js Framework by Wistity HQ
Description: Strapi aims to be an open-source Node.js rich framework for building applications and services. The framework allows for developers to write reusable application logic and spend less time on building infrastructure. The framework sits on top of Koa. It intends to combine small modules that work together to provide maintainability, and structural conventions to Node.js applications.

Framework Name: Adnois Node.js Framework by Aman Virk
Description: The Adonis framework is a MVC framework written in Node.js that intends to offer a customized resource for writing scalable applications by allowing for the defining of expressive routes and writing terminal commands.
The Sail.js Node.js Framework is designed to help developers create Node.js websites and applications. It provides methods for managing assets, uploading files, and managing features.

The Hapi framework's objective is to be a configuration-centric framework with built-in support for input validation, caching, authentication, and other essential facilities for building web and services applications. hapi enables developers to focus on writing reusable application logic in a highly modular and prescriptive approach.

Pomelo offers developers a scalable game server framework for node.js. The framework provides the development framework and many related components, including libraries and tools. Pomelo aims to be suitable for real-time web applications; its distributed architecture makes pomelo scale differently than other real-time frameworks.

Provides extensible common utility classes for rapid JSON API development. Offers the following functionality for abstration of middleware specific code for framework agnostic use; handling of request/response lifecycle; built in CRUD functionality via find, findOne, create, update, delete functions for various resources.
Noder Node.js framework aims to be a lightweight and flexible core to create a scalable API. Starting a project quickly with a modular API.
Restify is a Node.js framework that intends to offer a micro-framework for building REST APIs.

RhapsodyJS aims to be a HMVC framework that runs on top of Express 4 while also creating a RESTful API for models. Additionally, it supports sockets, middleware/policies system, and includes other features.

Koa aims to be an expressive HTTP middleware for node.js to make web applications and APIs less complicated to write. Koa's middleware stack flows in a stack-like manner, allowing developers to perform actions downstream then filter and manipulate the response upstream. Koa's use of generators also facilates readability and robustness to an application.

Framework Name: Percolator Node.js Framework by Gregg Caines
Description: Percolator aims to be a framework for building quality HTTP APIs in Node.js. It's features include quality, public-facing APIs, single page and mobile applications.

KeystoneJS is a Node.js framework that intends to provide a content management system and web application framework built onexpress and mongoose. Keystone offers the ability to create web sites and application, and comes with an auto-generated Admin UI.

Framework Name: Diet Node.js Framework by Ádám Halász
Description: diet.js aims to be a modular node.js web framework that offers scalable application and API development.

Framework Name: Restberry Node.js Framework by Mattias Eriksson
Description: Restberry intends to provide a framework for setting up RESTful JSON APIs with NodeJS. It allows for the indentification of models and setup CRUD API calls without the need for code writing to write code. API calls handle and identify issues as well as issue necessary HTTP responses and alerts to debug error responses. Restberry also provides authentication and permission checks and throws appropriate errors.

Framework Name: Loopback Node.js API Framework by StrongLoop
Description: The Loopback Node.js API Framework by StrongLoop provides a dynamic open source Node.js framework optimized for building end-to-end APIs for mobile, web, and other devices. The Loopback framework offers a set of Node.js modules that can be used together or independently to build applications. Developers can connect to multiple data sources, write business logic in Node.js, glue on top of existing services and data, connect using JS, iOS & Android SDKs, and much more.

Framework Name: Actionhero Node.js Framework by Evan Tahler
Description: The Actionhero.js framework aims to be a multi-transport Node.JS API Server with integrated cluster capabilities and delayed tasks..

Danf intends to provide a javascript/node.js full-stack isomorphic OOP framework allowing to code the same way on both client-side (browser) and server-side (node.js). It provides many features to produce scalable, maintainable, testable and performant applications.
The COKE Node.js framework aims to provide developers with a full stack MVC framework that expedites web development.
SocketStream aims to be a Node.js framework for realtime web applications.

Framework Name: Chocolatejs Node.js Framework by JC Levy
Description: Chocolatejs Node.js Framework aims to be a full stack and isomorphic Node.js web framework and online ide. The framework is an experimental Node.js web application framework built using Coffeescript.

Framework Name: Sane Stack Node.js Framework by Sane
Description: The Sane Stack is a Node.js framework that offers developers a Sails and Ember cli to faciliate application development. This framework is cited as being an early prototype with further developments to come.
Catberry is a Node.js framework that offers developers Flux architecture, isomorphic web-components and progressive rendering.

AllcountJS Node.js Framework intends to provide an open source full-stack Node.js framework for application development. The framework's objective is to be designed to build production-ready web and mobile business applications. It offers business applications such for basic ones like CRUD as well as the more complex such as CRM, inventory, accounting and other enterprise systems that have domain objects with different views.

Koa is a Node.js web framework that allows users to ditch callbacks and increase error handling by leveraging generators. It's designed by the same team that designed Express. Koa was made to be smaller, more expressive, and more robust.

Framework Name: Mediator JavaScript Framework by Jack Lawson
Description: Mediator is a JavaScript framework that intends to provide a class that allows a developer to register, unregister, and call subscriber methods to help event-based, asyncronous programming. The framework's purpose is to make the usage of WebSockets, Ajax calls, DOM events, or other asynchronous operations easy to maintain and test.

Framework Name: 140 Medley JavaScript Framework by Honza Pokorny
Description: The 140 Medley JavaScript Framework by Honza Pokorny aims to be a micro-framework or a collection of small, helpful utilities for common javascript tasks.
The Rococo JavaScript Framework offers developers a strict subset of Javascript (BlackScript). BlackScript is like Javascript but has no:

The Janis JavaScript frameworks aims to be a lightweight framework that provides animations via CSS transitions for modern browsers on the web as well as mobile devices. The goal of the framework is to organize commonly used methods of animating DOM elements in JavaScript.

Framework Name: Lotus Ruby Framework by Luca Guidi
Description: The Lotus Ruby Framework offers developers an Object Oriented Programming option to web development,

The Padrinorb ruby Framework's goal is offer developers core principles of the Sinatra Ruby Framework while creating a standard library of tools, helpers and functions that will make Sinatra suitable for increasingly complex applications.

Framework Name: NYNY Ruby Framework by Andrei Lisnic
Description: The NYNY Ruby Framework offers developers a micro web framework for testing applications on modern browsers. It's features include Rack middleware that allows for the use inside of Sinatra, Rails, and other Rack-based apps and being ~300 LOC in size.

Framework Name: Grape Ruby Framework by Ruby Grape
Description: The Grape Ruby Framework allows for the building of lightweight APIs with Ruby when a larger framework like Ruby on Rails isn't needed. It aims to be a REST-like API micro-framework built to work with existing web application frameworks by providing DSL to provide APIs. The framework's features include: built-in support for common conventions such as multiple formats, subdomain/prefix restriction, and versioning.

Framework Name: Nancy Ruby Framework by Guillermo Iguaran
Description: The Nancy Framework aims to be a minimal Ruby microframework for web development inspired in the Sinatra and Cuba frameworks. The framework's features include: routes such as support for get, post, put, patch, delete, options, head; set basic filters/callbacks with the before/after methods; and template rendering and caching through Tilt or ERB from stdlib.

Framework Name: Cuba Ruby Framework by Michel Martens
Description: The Cuba Ruby Framework is a microframework that offers developers a mapper for Rack applications, inspired by Rum, a unified mapper for Rack applications.

Framework Name: Scorched Ruby Framework by Tom Wardrop
Description: The Scorched framework is a Ruby framework that aims to be a generic, DRY, light-weight web framework for Ruby. It offers a generic set of constructs for processing HTTP requests, with websites and applications of different scales can be used to be built.

Framework Name: Stapes JavaScript Framework by Hay Kranen
Description: The Stapes.js JavaScript framework aims to allow the design of an application to be objective on the setup and style of coding. The framework allows for developers to code using models, views and controllers, modules, jQuery, Zepto, React, and many others.

Framework Name: Wru JavaScript Framework by Andrea Giammarchi
Description: Wru is a JavaScript framework that intends to offer an essential, general purpose test framework compatible with web environment, node.js,Rhino, and PhantomJS.
The Nerve JavaScript Framework by Jstandish aims to be an asynchronous javascript micro framework for event broadcasts along routes and channels.

Framework Name: Guggenheim JavaScript Framework by Will McKenzie
Description: The JavaScript framework Guggenheim.js offers developers a framework for agnostic plugin to create interactive galleries. It uses CSS3 animation (with a fallback to Javascript) to create animated filtering, reordering and pagination of a gallery.

Framework Name: PatternLab PHP Framework by Pattern Lab
Description: The PHP version of Pattern Lab aims to be a static site generator. The framework combines platform-agnostic assets, like the Mustache-based patterns and the JavaScript-based viewer, with a PHP-based "builder" that builds the Pattern Lab site. By making it a static site generator, Pattern Lab aims to separate patterns, data, and presentation from build logic.

Framework Name: Styleguide Node.js Framework by Lars Kappert
Description: The Node.js framework Style Guide aims to be a simple styleguide framework. It offers developers aninstall component-styleguide into a styleguide project with minimal impact. The frameworks realted to http://patternlab.io.
The Nuclear JavaScript Framework by Optimizely aims to be a reactive flux built with ImmutableJS data structures.

Framework Name: JSBlocks JavaScript Framework by Antonio Stoilkov
Description: The JSBlocks JavaScript Framework by Antonio Stoilkov offers developers a user interface for complex single-page applications using a server-side rendered framework

The JavaScript Framework WebRx aims to be a Javascript MVVM-Framework built on ReactiveX for Javascript (RxJs) that combines functional-reactive programming with Observable-driven declarative Data-Binding, Features also include templating and Client-Side Routing.

Framework Name: Phaser JavaScript Framework by Richard Davey
Description: The Phaser JavaScript Framework by Richard Davey is intended to be a free 2D game framework for making HTML5 games for desktop and mobile web browsers, supporting Canvas and WebGL rendering.

Framework Name: Opentip JavaScript Framework by Matias Meno
Description: The Opentip JavaScript Framework by Matias Meno aims to be a javascript tooltip. It offers uses for adapters to make the framework available for all major frameworks and provides a native adapter that works without a framework.

Framework Name: Maria JavaScript Framework by Peter Michaux
Description: The MVC framework is intended for JavaScript applications. The framework is aimed at developers who use real MVC such as The Smalltalk MVC and The Gang of Four MVC. The framework is written in JavaScript.

The Qunit JavaScript Framework by jQuery aims to be a powerful JavaScript unit testing framework. The framework is intended for jQuery UI and jQuery Mobile projects and allows for testing generic JavaScript code including the framework itself.
The Derby Framework offers developers a MVC framework to write realtime, collaborative applications that run in both Node.js and browsers.

Framework Name: Mithril JavaScript Framework by Leo Horie
Description: The Mithril JavaScript Framework by Leo Horie aims to be a client-side MVC framework, The framework offers developers a tool to organize code in a way that facilitates maintenance and organization.

Framework Name: Noduino JavaScript Framework by Sebastian Müller
Description: The JavaScript framework by Sebastian Müller allows for developers to create a JavaScript and Node.js Framework for accessing basic Arduino controls from Web Applications using HTML5, Socket.IO and Node.js.

Framework Name: Prototype JavaScript Framework by Sam Stephenson
Description: Prototype is a JavaScript framework that aims to ease development of dynamic web applications. It offers a familiar class-style OO framework, extensive Ajax support, higher-order programming constructs, and easy DOM manipulation.

The Aurelia Framework aims to be a library that offers part of the Aurelia platform and contains the aurelia framework which brings together all the required core aurelia libraries into an application-building platform.

Babylon.js aims to be a complete JavaScript framework for building 3D games with HTML 5 and WebGL. A web browser is required to run the framework, and it currently supports Internet Explorer 11+, Firefox 4+, Google Chrome 9+, Opera 12+ and others.

Framework Name: ColorBox JavaScript Framework by Jack Moore
Description: The ColorBox JavaScript Framework by Jack Moore offers developers a customizable lightbox plugin for jQuery.

Framework Name: Holder JavaScript Framework by Ivan Malopinsky
Description: The Holder.js Framework aims to render image placeholders entirely in a browser. The framework offers customer colors, fonts, resizing behavior, and rendering engine.

FlexSlider JavaScript Framework aims to be a responsive Jquery slider toolkit. The framework offers developers support for all major browsers, callback API, multiple slider support, and customer navigation options.

Framework Name: Interact.js JavaScript Framework by Taye A
Description: The Interact.js JavaScript Framework aims to offer developers a testing environment that allows them to drop, resize and multi-touch gestures with inertia and snapping for modern browsers. Features include cross browser and device support, interaction with SVG elements, and others.

The Nightwatch.js Framework aims to be a Node.js based End-to-End (E2E) testing solution for browser based apps and websites. It uses the Selenium WebDriver API to perform commands and assertions on DOM elements.

Framework Name: Applcelerator Titanium Mobile JavaScript Framework by Appcelerator
Description: The Titanium framework aims to provide a platform for web developers to build cross-platform, native mobile applications using JavaScript. Currently, Titanium supports mobile smartphone operating systems such as Apple iPhone, Google's Android, and Mobile Web. Other platforms, such as Windows Phone, are currently in development.

The Moobile JavaScript Framework by Moobile aims to be a mobile application framework based on Mootools. The framework requires Safari or Chrome to be ultilized as well as a broiler plate for MooTools.

EmbedJS is a JavaScript framework that aims to be targeted at embedded devices (mobile phones, TVs, etc.). The frameworks offers a different approach by shipping just the code needed for each device. This feature results in less code going over the wire and branching at runtime as well as less memory usage.

Iconic JavaScript Framework by Iconic is currently free and open source. The framework aims to offer a library of mobile-optimized HTML, CSS and JS components, gestures, and tools for building highly interactive apps. It is built with Sass and optimized for AngularJS.

Framework Name: Zepto JavaScript Framework by Thomas Fuchs
Description: Zepto aims to be a minimalist JavaScript library/framework for modern browsers with a largely jQuery-compatible API. This requires Node.js installation prior to use.

Framework Name: JQTouch JavaScript Framework by Sencha Labs
Description: jQTouch is a JavaScript plugin/framework that aims to work with either Zepto.js or jQuery, and includes animations, navigation, and themes for mobile WebKit browsers (as found in iOS, Android, BlackBerry, and WebOS). Features includes customization, theme support, callback functions, Zepto integration and many others.
PhoneGap JavaScript Framework aims to be an open source framework that allows developers to create mobile apps using standardized web APIs for platforms.

Framework Name: Twelve-Space JavaScript Framework by Kevin Mack
Description: The Twelve-Space JavaScript Framework by Kevin Mack aims to be a Sass-based, BEM, OOCSS framework for creating DOM modules. This framework is written in JavaScript.

jQuery.my aims to be a plugin that binds HTML controls with underlying javascript object using declarative MVVM style manifest. Bindings are bi-directional and real-time. jQuery.my recognizes standard HTML controls as well as composite controls rendered by jQuery Mobile, nearly all jQuery UI widgets, Redactor, Ace, CodeMirror, Select2 and others.

ChocolateChip-UI aims to be a JavaScript framework for making mobile Web apps. It has three components: semantic HTML5 markup, CSS and JavaScript. Using the framework requires a familiarity with JavaScript so users can utilize features such as templates, Ajax requests and handle callbacks for user interaction. ChocolateChip-UI requires jQuery.

The RaptorJS aims to be a JavaScript module bundler that also provides first-level support for delivering JavaScript, CSS, images and other assets to the browser. Supported optimizations: Bundling, Code splitting, Lazy loading, Compression, and several others.

The Watir Framework aims to be an open-source (BSD) family of Ruby libraries for automating web browsers. It supports develper's apps regardless of the technology it is developed in. The framework supports testing in Internet Explorer on Windows, Firefox and Chrome on Windows, Mac and Linux.

Yeti aims to be a Framework that tests frameworks. It allows for the automation of testing for various test frameworks. Yeti attempts to test a dev box (where it works by itself) to a CI system (where it launches browsers with Selenium) without changing existing tests. The framework requires Node.js.

Framework Name: Zombiejs JavaScript Framework by Assaf Arkin
Description: Zombie.js aims to be a lightweight framework for testing client-side JavaScript code in a simulated environment. Its biggest feature is that is does not require a browser for testing. Installation requires oi.js.

Framework Name: Karma JavaScript Framework by Karma Runner
Description: The aim of the Karma JavaScript Framework is to bring instant feedback testing to developers. Its features include: testing on real devices, remote workflow control, continuous integration, and others.

Framework Name: Casperjs JavaScript Framework by Nicolas Perriault
Description: CasperJS aims to be a navigation scripting & testing utility for PhantomJS and SlimerJS. The framework facilitates the process of defining a full navigation scenario and provides functionality, methods & syntaxic sugar for doing common tasks. Such tasks include: defining and ordering navigantion steps; filing forms, clicking links, capturing screenshots, logging events and several others. This framework is written in JavaScript.

Framework Name: Phantomjs JavaScript Framework by Ariya Hidayat
Description: PhantomJS aims to be a headless WebKit that is scriptable with a JavaScript API. Its features include native support for various web standards: DOM handling, CSS selector, JSON, Canvas, and SVG. PhantomJS can be used to test workflow of various open-source projects: Bootstrap, CodeMirror, Ember.js, jQuery Mobile, Less.js, Modernizr, YUI3, and others. The framework is written in JavaScript.

Framework Name: State Machine JavaScript Framework by Jake Gordon
Description: The State Machine Framework offers developers a standalone javascript micro-framework that provides a finite state machine. This framework is written JavaScript.

Framework Name: AngularJS JavaScript Router Framework by Angular-UI
Description:
The AngularJS JavaScript Router Framework by Angular-UI is a de-facto solution to flexible routing with nested views for the AngularJS API. This routing framework allows users to organize parts of interfaces into a state machine. The states are bound to named, nested and parallel views, allowing for powerful management of the user's application interfaces.
The AngularJS API allows developers to access and integrate the functionality of AngularJS with other applications and to create new applications.

Framework Name: xCSS JavaScript Framework by Anton Pawlik
Description: The xCSS JavaScript Framework by Anton Pawlik aims to be a straightforward and object-oriented workflow when developing complex style cascades. It allows for developers to more easily develop and write CSS applications and includes a variety of other features.
The GroundworkCSS Framework allows for developers to use HTML5, CSS and Javascript toolkits. The Framework aims create accessible web apps that work on different devices.

Framework Name: Unsematic CSS Framework by Nathan Smith
Description: The Unsematic CSS Framework by Nathan Smith aims to be a fluid grid for mobile, tablet, and desktop application developers.

Framework Name: Tuktuk CSS Framework by Javi Jiménez
Description: The Tuktuk CSS Framework by Javi Jiménez allows for developers to create responsive front-end framework that creates extensible sites. Features include: CSS3 powered, and Object Oriented CSS: The aim of this framework is to encourage code reuse and create stylesheets that can be added to and maintained.

Framework Name: Fluidable CSS Framework by Andri Sigurðsson
Description: The Fluidable CSS Framework by Andri Sigurðsson aims to be a mobile first, responsive grid system. It is standalone, lightweight & built using LESS.
The Ink CSS Framework by SAPO aims to be an HTML5/CSS3 framework for design and prototyping.
The Kickoff CSS Framework by Kickoff aims to be a lightweight front-end framework for creating scalable, responsive sites.

Framework Name: Cascade CSS Framework by John Slegers
Description: The Cascade CSS Framework by John Slegers allows developers to split CSS into seperate files based on features rather than selectors as well as implementt a modifier design pattern inspired by SMACCS and OOCSS,

Framework Name: Jeet CSS Framework by Mojo Tech
Description: The Jeet CSS Framework by MojoTech aims to be a grid system with the option to integrate fractions (or float numbers) as context that generates a percentage based width and gutter for grids.

Framework Name: Responsive Broilerplate CSS Framework by fernando monteiro
Description: The Responsive Broilerplate CSS Framework by fernando monteiro aims to be a lightweight (3kb) cross browser grid system made with three main classes and 12 columns.

Framework Name: Susy CSS Framework by Eric Suzzane
Description: The Susy CSS Framework allows developers to make custom layouts with CSS. The framework requires Sass.

Framework Name: Inuit CSS Framework by Harry Roberts
Description: The Inuit CSS Framework by Harry Roberts aims to provide a scalable, Sass-based, BEM, OOCSS framework. The framework is geared toward being less code heavy, and for developers that are providing abstraction and an OO approach. the framework's features include: design patterns, nestable, fluid grids; a double-stranded heading hierarchy; sprites; buttons and others.
TopCoat CSS Framework by TopCoat aims to be a BEM oriented, themeable and responsive framework written in CSS.

Vert.x Core is an open source framework for building responsive apps in the Java Virtual Machine (JVM). Vert.x Core is a suite of APIs that handle tasks like: writing TCP clients and servers, writing HTTP clients and servers, shared data, datagram Sockets, DNS client, file system access, clustering and more. Although based in Java, the Vert.x also offers idiomatic API equivalents in Ruby, JavaScript, Ruby and Groovy. See the project page for detailed descriptions of Vert.x's capabilities and full API documentation. The project is developed with the Eclipse Foundation and licensed under the Eclipse Public License 1.0 and Apache License 2.0.

The Face++ iOS SDK by Face++ offers interaction with the API in Objective-C language with the goal to aggregate image recognition features into an Apple application. Resources include step by step instructions to integrate FacePlusPlus SDK into an iOS project. Text on GitHub available in English and Chinese.

Framework Name: Cloud Elements Python SDK by MobileWorks
Description: This is the Python SDK for Cloud Elements allowing developers to access and integrate the functionality of Cloud Elements with other applications through Python. Cloud Elements is an API management and integration platform that helps developers design, manage, and integrate their APIs.

Framework Name: Common Works Registration Python Framework by Weso
Description: This framework provides access to the Common Works Registration (CWR) through Python. CWR is the standard for registration and revision of musical works.

Framework Name: Crossroads Internet of Things iOS Framework by Feeney Wireless
Description: Crossroads is an Internet of Things framework that aims to simplify big data. It is targeted to vendors, devices, and platforms. This framework in Objective-C is available contacting Feeney Wireless, a company based in Oregon, USA dedicated to facilitate the Internet of Things. For more information, visit http://feeneywireless.com/company/contact_us

Framework Name: Crossroads Internet of Things Android Framework by Feeney Wireless
Description: Feeney Wireless, known by providing Internet of Things services, recently released Crossroads, a framework that aims to simplify IoT for big data projects. The framework in Java language for Android development is available contacting the company at http://feeneywireless.com/company/contact_us

The PencilBlue Node.js Framework allows developers to access and integrate the functionality of PencilBlue with other applications. PencilBlue is a Node.js content management system for blogs and websites of all sizes.

The Eskimo Node.js Framework allows developers to create Node.js powered APIs, applications, and other Node.js products. Eskimo offers solutions and tools to developers to build APIs, applications, and more in Node.js.

Framework Name: Mathjs Node.js & JavaScript Framework by Jos de Jong
Description: The Mathjs Node.js and JavaScript Framework provides a math library for Node.js and JavaScript. Math.js provides a solution to integrate and work with big and complex numbers, units, and matrices in applications.

The Spring Framework by Spring is a framework that provides developers with models for programming and configuration of Java-based enterprise applications. This framework also provides foundations for all of the other Spring projects.

TinEye offers reverse image search services to maintain a person's reputation or a brand's image. While match engine finds duplicate of an image, mobile engine connects the physical with the digital world using recognition capacities. This is the official Python library for the Commercial API, which allows to read and write data related to copyright compliance and image moderation.

The PSK PHP Framework aims to provide tools for routing, API versioning, data transformation, authentication, documentation and testing. PSX allows for the building of a REST API around an existing application or create a new one from scratch.

Meteor JavaScript Framework aims for building modern web applications. The Framework allows for With Meteor writing apps in pure JavaScript that send data over the wire instead of HTML using open-source libraries.

Framework Name: HiFramework PHP Framework by Diego Mariani
Description: The HiFramework is a lightweight PHP framework built to create php applications.

Framework Name: Wee JavaScript Framework by Wee Power
Description: The Wee JavaScript frameworks aims to be a mobile-first CSS framework with reset, base, and Less mixin library features. It is written in JavaScript.
TourCMS Angular.js SDK by TourCMS provides developers an Angular framework to work with the TourCMS API.

Framework Name: Cerebral JavaScript Framework by Christian Alfoni
Description: The Cerebral JavaScript Framework aims to be a skeleton framework for application development. The framework is currently in the preview phase. It is written in JavaScript.
The Zikula PHP Framework by Zikula offers a web based application framework, fully extensible by modules, plugins and themes. It is written in PHP.
The Symfony PHP Framework by SensioLabs aims to provide a standard foundation for building PHP applications.

The BEAR.Resource aims to be a Hypermedia framework that allows for resources to behave as objects. Features include allowing objects to have RESTful web service benefits such as client-server, uniform interface, statelessness, resource expression with mutual connectivity and layered components. The Framework is written in PHP.

The BEAR.Sunday PHP Framework aims to be a resource orientated framework with a REST centered architecture, implementing Dependency Injection and Aspect Orientated Programming' at its core. The frameowrk is written in PHP.

Framework Name: Furtive CSS JavaScript Framework by Jon Otander
Description: The Furtive CSS JavaScript Framework by Jon Otander is a JavaScript framework that allows for application developement using CSS.

T3 JavaScript Framework aims to be a client-side JavaScript framework for building large-scale web applications. Its design is based on the principles of Scalable JavaScript Application Architecture. It is written in JavaScript.
The Deployd JavaScript Framework by Deployd aims to be an API building tool that provides ready-made functionality. This framework is written in JavaScript.

The iCloudDocumentSync project by iRare Media integrates iCloud into iOS documents. With this framework, users are able to sync, upload, manage, and remove documents from iCloud. The idea is to simplify the process. Sam's project features drag and drop from iCloud framework, delegate methods, iOS sample app, and frequent updates. Developers are invited to contribute to his work.
This Diffbot Client by Diffbot supports Dart programming language interaction with Diffbot APIs.

The Materialize JavaScript Framework was created and designed by Google, Material Design is a design language that combines principles of design. Google's goal is to develop a system of design that allows for a unified user experience across all their products on any platform.

Framework Name: Mezzanine CMS Framework for Django by stephenmcd
Description: The Mezzanine CMS Django framework provides MVC architecture, ORM, tempting, caching, automatic admin interface, hierarchical page navigation, save in draft or preview, schedule publishing, drag-and-drop page ordering, WYSIWYG editing, in-line page editing, drag-and-drop HTML5 forms builder with CSV export, SEO friendly URLs and meta data, shopping card module, multiple integrations, and customization features for the Mezzanine API.

Framework Name: Docker Remote PHP SDK by Stage1
Description: This is a PHP SDK for working with Docker's API. Docker offers an open platform for distributed app development. This PHP SDK is still under development, and does not yet support all features of the API. Installation via Composer is recommended. See the documentation for versioning information and info regarding the further development of the SDK.
The Kohana PHP Framework by Kohana is a web development framework that allows for the building of applications. The framework is written in PHP5.

The Sails framework is a web framework that allows developers to build custom, enterprise-grade Node.js apps. It aims to resemble the MVC architecture from frameworks like Ruby on Rails, but with support for the more modern, data-oriented style of web app development. This Framework is for Node.js.

The Play Java Framework by Play allows for a high-productivity Java web application framework that integrates the components and API for web application development. The framework is written in Java and is available in Scala.

Phalcon PHP Framework by Phalcon is an open source, full stack framework for PHP written as a C-extension, optimized for high performance. Phalcon is loosely coupled, allowing for objects as glue components based on the needs of an application.

Slim is a lightweight micro framework that developers can use to build web applications and RESTful APIs in PHP. Features include a router, a resource locator and DI container, template rendering with custom views and more.

The Sensu Ruby Framework by Sensu is an open source framework that aims to provide a monitoring framework. By providing an agent, message bus, & event processor, Sensu enables developers and operations teams to compose telemetry systems to meet business specifications.

Framework Name: Flickr iOS Framework by David Casserly
Description: The Flickr iOS framework by David Casserly has been created to access the Flickr API just like the currently used gallery pro iPad app. With this framework, users have two options to call methods: by string or by classes. It does not support Mac OS X. Available usage with API notes and authentication. Developers will be able to load interesting photos using the generated Flickr API model classes. This framework is written in Objective-C.

Framework Name: Cloudmade Geocoding Static Framework by Landon Fuller
Description: Cloudmade Geocoding is a system that provides predictive learning, map data enrichment, and navigation & guidance in connected cars. Cloudmade blog encourages users to work with a static framework available on developer's Landon Fuller site. This framework includes links, sections, and archives. This work was created to interact with iPhones.

Framework Name: Cloudmade Geocoding Mac OS Framework by Apple
Description: The Cloudmade Geocoding API supports connected car content features such as map portals and driver analytics. This OS framework created by Apple can be useful for developers who want to build in Xcode to automate structures for Cloudmade according to their blog. Available directory, configuration, and compatibility.

Framework Name: PSX PHP Framework by Christoph Kappestein
Description: PSX is a framework written in PHP to create RESTful APIs. It provides tools to handle routing, API versioning, data transformation, authentication, documentation and testing. With PSX, developers can build an REST API around an existing application or create a new one.

Framework Name: Ensembles Core Data iOS Framework by Drew McCormack
Description: The Ensembles Core Data iOS Framework by Drew McCormack aims to extend Apple's Core Data framework to add peer-to-peer synchronization for Mac OS and iOS. Multiple SQLite persistent stores can be coupled together via a file synchronization platform like iCloud or Dropbox. The framework can be readily extended to support any service capable of moving files between devices, including custom servers. It is written in Objective-C.

Framework Name: iOS Charts Framework by Daniel Cohen Gindi
Description: The iOS Charts Framework by Daniel Cohen Gindideveloping is for both platforms, as the learning curve is singleton- it happens only once, and the code stays very similar so developers don't have to go around and re-invent the app to produce the same output with a different library. This framework is written in Objective-C.

Framework Name: ROAD iOS Framework by EPam Systems
Description: The ROAD iOS Framework by EPam Systems is a set of reusable components taking advantage of extra dimension Attribute-Oriented Programming adds. This framework is written in Objective-C.
The CocoaLumberJack iOS Framework By CocoaLumberJack is a logging framework for Mac and iOS. Written in Objective-C.
The Mantle iOS Framework by Mantle is a model framework for Cocoa and Cocoa Touch. It is written in Objective-C.

The AFNetworking iOS Framework by AFNetworking is a networking library for iOS and Mac OS X. It's built on top of the Foundation URL Loading System, extending high-level networking abstractions built into Cocoa. It has a modular architecture with well-designed, feature-rich APIs. The framework is written in Objective-C.
The DFImage Manager by Alexander Grebenyuk is an iOS framework for loading, caching, processing, displaying and preheating images. The framework is written in Objective-C.

Framework Name: UiImage iOS Framework by Mad Dog Software
Description: The UiImage iOS Framework by Mad Dog Software has IOS UIImage processing functions using the vDSP/Accellerate framework for speed. The framework is written in Objective-C.

Framework Name: GPUImage iOS Framework by Brad Larson
Description: The GPUImage framework is a BSD-licensed iOS library that allows developers to apply GPU-accelerated filters and other effects to images, live camera video, and movies. Further, GPUImage allows for writing custom filters, supports deployment to iOS 4.0, and has a simpler interface. This framework is written in Objective-C.

The WURFL is a Device Description Repository (DDR), or framework that enables applications to map HTTP requests to a description of the capability of the mobile device that requests the page. This framework is written in PHP,

Framework Name: Google BigQuery Go SDK by Google
Description: This Go client is auto generated by Google for use with their APIs, including BigQuery. The BigQuery API harnesses Google's major processing power to quickly query append-only data tables with SQL-like commands. See the project documentation for details on installing the API and importing the Go client.

Framework Name: AddThis Web Service Framework by AddThis
Description: The AddThis Web Service Framework by AddThis describes the common properties of all the APIs available on http://api.addthis.com.

RestKit is an Objective-C framework for iOS that aims to make interacting with RESTful web services in a simplified format. It combines HTTP request/response API with a object mapping system that reduces the need for code writing.
The eMobc IOS Framework allows for the development of native apps based in XML.
The eMobc Android Framework allows for the creation of native apps based in XML in Android. The framework is written in JavaScript.

Framework Name: Nimbus iOS Framework by Jeff Verkoeyen
Description: The Nimbus is an iOS framework is a whose feature based framework that allows for problem solving when developing iOS applications. The framework is written in Objective-C.

The PowerMock is a Java framework that allows you to unit test code normally regarded as untestable. PowerMock is a framework that extends other mock libraries such as EasyMock with more capabilities. PowerMock uses a custom classloader and bytecode manipulation to enable mocking of static methods, constructors, final classes and methods, private methods, removal of static initializers and more.

Framework Name: Core Plot iOS Framework by Core Plot
Description: The Core Plot is a plotting framework for Mac OS X and iOS. It provides 2D visualization of data, and is integrated with Apple technologies like Core Animation, Core Data, and Cocoa Bindings. The framework is written in Objective-C.
The Box2D C++ Framework is a 2D rigid body physics engine, written in C++ by Erin Catto. Box2D is developed on Windows using Visual C++. Ports are also available for Flash, Java, C#, Python.
The TouchXML Framework is an iOS framework written in Objective-C as a replacement for Cocoa's NSXML* cluster of classes. It is based on the commonly available Open Source libxml2 library.

Framework Name: Facebook React Native Framework by Facebook
Description: The Facebook React Native Framework by Facebook allows developers to build quality applications on native platforms using React and JavaScript.

Framework Name: Gem Bitcoin Python Library by BitVault
Description: The Gem Bitcoin Python Library by BitVault allows developers to integrate the Gem Bitcoin API's methods into their Python applications.

Framework Name: Sauce Labs PHP Framework by Sauce Labs
Description: The Sauce Labs PHP Framework provides automated application testing. The SDK is written in PHP.

Framework Name: USA ePAY Perl Framework by CPAN
Description: The USA ePAY Perl Framework by CPAN is an online payment framework for USA ePay and a generic module for processing payments through online credit card processors, electronic cash systems, etc. This framework is written in Perl.
The Wepay Python Framework by Wepay allows developers to build on their API and add payments into applications. This framework is written in Python.
Use this JavaScript SDK from Acision to add video and voice calling, messaging, content sharing, and other WebRTC capabilities into your web and mobile applications.

The OAuth Django Framework by eofs makes it easy for developers to access the OAuth API using the Django REST Framework. This framework requires Python 2.7 or 3.3, Django 1.7+, Django Rest Framework 3.1+, and OAuthLib 0.6.0.

The Ionic Javascript Framework by Ionicis a HTML5 native app development framework that allows developers to build native-feeling mobile apps with web technologies like HTML, CSS, and Javascript. Ionic is focused mainly on the look and feel, and UI interaction of your app. Ionic recommends AngularJS in order to work at its fully. .

The Yii PHP Framework by Yii is a free, open source project released under the terms of the BSD License. It provides Web application development framework written in PHP5 that promotes DRY design and allows for development. Yii works to streamline application development and helps developers with their application development.

A PERL SDK for interfacing with SendGrid's SMTP API. This SDK provides a wrapper for custom SMTP fields as well as a way to manipulate filter and app settings. SendGrid is a cloud-based platform for sending and managing email, and generating email analytics.

The Google Affiliate Network Java Library allows developers to integrate Google Affiliate Network data into their Java applications. Developers can add the library to their projects in Maven or Gradle using the provided code, or they can download a zip file containing the required jars.

The Skeleton framework allows developers a framework for smaller, responsive CSS projects that don't need the utility of larger frameworks. Skeleton only styles standard HTML elements and includes a grid. The framework offers itself as a starting point with with UI and roughly 400 lines of CSS unminified (with comments), and has no compiling or installing.

Use this framework for building iOS and OSX App.net applications. The framework offers 100% App.net and features and multiuser support. ADNKit's only external dependency is AFNetworking, a networking library. See the framework wiki for detailed installation and implementation documentation.
This Python language framework allows interaction between Django model interface and Twitter API objects.

The LifePics service provides photo finishing and printing, including online storage and sharing of images. The LifePics Android SDK provides tools that enable developers to integrate the LifePics OPEN (Open Photo Ecommerce Network) API into Android applications. This will allow select pictures to be printed automatically from within a user's Android application. The SDK requires a LifePics developer key for use, and supports Android 2.3.3 and later. Instructions detail how to install and implement the SDK using Android Studio.

Kraken is a framework in Node.js language that assists in the application development process with security and scalability. Although this tool can be used independently, users can benefit from 4 modules that include Lusca, an application security, Kappa with NPM Proxy, Makara with Dust i18n, and Adaro with Js context. Using Kraken, example projects include a shopping cart, passport integration, localization, and A/B testing.

Laravel is a framework in PHP language that invites developers to contribute for continuous improvement. Resources aim to educate users to create projects. Documentation on the Laravel website demonstrates installation, configuration, routing, and controllers. Additionally, it displays authentication, events, localization, security, unit testing, and validation. These guides can help to develop original work or practice over projects like the ones presented in the website. Such examples include Laravel Art, Laravel Cashier, Laravel Homestead, and Laravel Website.

Dogpatch is a framework designed to test HTTP-accessible APIs. The package is written in PHP using curl. The framework was originally created by the team at NodeSocket to help in testing the Commando.io API. The framework supports basic authentication, SSL support, custom requests, and redirection up to 10 levels.

Gisgraphy is a framework that helps users integrate geocoding services into their Java applications and webservices. The data provided comes from GeoNames and OpenStreetMap. Users may also add their own data. Results from Gisgraphy can be output in XML, JSON, PHP, Python, Ruby, YAML, GeoRSS, and Atom.

This library allows developers using Solaris to create their Bloomberg API with Perl. Solaris developers should note that these libraries can only be used with the Bloomberg Server API and B-Pipe data feed products (not the Desktop API). The Bloomberg API provides free, unrestricted access to raw financial data on current market trades (either real-time or delayed), reference data on historical information, and records of intraday trading. As part of their Open Market Data Initiative the library is offered under a "free-use" license, which allows unrestricted access of the interface's header files, documentation, and programming examples.

Rest.li is an end to end framework optimal for building RESTful APIs. Some of the features of this framework combine approachable APIs for writing non-blocking client and server code using ParSeq, type-safe development using generated data and client bindings, and JAX-RS inspired annotation driven server side resource development. LinkedIn, the professional social media network, uses Rest.li due to its client-side load balance, consistency with services, and the development possibilities of new features. The requirements to work with Rest.li include Java 1.6+ and Gradle 1.8+ or SBT 0.13.0+. A step by step tutorial shows example source code, creation of server, and creation of client.

Java API for RESTful Services (JAX-RS) started as part of the Gen incubator, a community of developers who create projects for the general public. The website offers drafts of the API, specifications, and mailing lists to communicate with the expert group. The latest API proposals are available on the wiki site. Releases include JAX-RS 2.0, JAX-RS 1.1, JAX-RS 1.0, and JAX-RS 0.x. The newest version, JAX-RS 2.0, provides portable APIs to develop, expose, and access web applications in REST. Web resources and provider extensions are available. In the Java community site, users can view the different stages of the project along with links to access every result.

Django REST framework in Python language aims to facilitate the creation of Web APIs. The requirements to work with Django include Python 2.6.5+, 2.7, 3.2, 3.3, 3.4 and Django 1.4.11+, 1.5.5+, 1.6, 1.7. Installation options are available either by using pip or by cloning from GitHub. Django has been used by Mozilla and Eventbrite. To visualize how this framework can fit into a developer's practices, an example is available with steps to follow. Benefits to develop include community support, customization, and extensive documentation.

Flask is a micro framework for Python supported by a BSD license. The documentation available on the website or downloadable in PDF or zipped HTML, contains built in developer and debugger, integrated unit testing support, RESTful request dispatching, Jinja2 templates, support for secure cookies, and WSGI 1.0 compliance. Sources of the examples of a microblog and a twitter clone made with Flask can be found on redirected links to GitHub. To contribute as developer, improver, or debugger Flask can be contacted on the IRC channel, the Feedback website, and the issue tracker.

Microsoft ASP.NET Web API is a framework in .NET language that aims to facilitate HTTP building services in browsers and mobile devices. Two installing options are available: visual studio express 2013 and visual studio 2013 community. With the goal to instruct developers about the possibilities of application development, a tutorial has been published with a downloadable complete project. This project includes the steps to create an API web assignment that returns a list of products using JQuery. The specifications of adding a model, adding a controller, calling the Web API, and running the application are available for practice. Besides the rehearsal part, the site offers the following resources: mobile clients, routing, OData, serialization, testing/debugging, error handling, authentication, security, and API reference.

Sinatra is an open source framework in Ruby. It is a domain-specific language that aims to accelerate web application development. Sinatra 1.3.0 version offers the feature of a streaming API while digesting differences between evented and sequential Rack servers. To imagine the possibilities of development, readers should consider that Apple, BBC, LinkedIn, and GitHub are some of the companies that use Sinatra. A book written by Alan Harris and Konstantin Haase, "Sinatra: up and running" is available for purchase. This resource contains additional information related to installation, routing, application/delegation, modular applications, and implementation of a blog engine.

Fortune.js is a framework in Node.js language. This framework can prototype hypermedia APIs with JSON protocol. Some of the available resources include guides, docs, examples, and issue management. Particularly, the guide shows instructional procedures that help to create applications. For example, the specifications sections of defining resources, defining association between resources, before and after associations within resources, and advanced usage aim to differentiate the purpose of the framework. In this case, Fortune.js is not an MVC framework, but a JSON view response specified by the JSON API spec.

Expressjs.com is a framework in Node.js language. Thanks to the resources available that include an introductory guide, a general guide, and a community guide, Expressjs.com aims to facilitate development for desktop and mobile applications. The introductory guide offers installation, express generator, and FAQ. The general guide presents error handling, debugging express, express behind proxies, and middleware. The community guide is under the resources tab. It shows examples, issues, and a Google Group with over 5,000 discussions.

Eskimo is a framework that helps developers construct Node.js powered APIs, online retail stores, and other applications. Eskimo is a boilerplate framework, providing simple scaffolding for rapidly developing prototypes and minimum viable products. The framework depends on Mongoose for NoSQL, Jade for HTML, Bookshelf for MySQL/MariaDB/PostgreSQL, and less LESS as a pre-processor and for middleware routing. The framework is customizable with a configuration file that enables the developer to exclude unnecessary parts.

The Freedomotic Framework is an open-source, flexible, and secure development framework. It's functions can help in building and managing modern smart spaces for individuals and business users. Freedomotic's framework works to provide solutions to creating building automation systems, small retail environments and more, and has the ability to be integrated with other automated technologies.

Zend is a Framework on PHP. Some of the features include security, modularity, and community. To start with Zend Framework 2, it is recommendable to run at least PHP 5.3.23 with Apache web server and MySQL via PDO extension. Resources include a getcomposer link to create a project from scratch using the skeleton application available on Github, modules to organize a main application specific within each module, routing and controllers to build an inventory, database to run SQL statements, styling to remove any copyright messages, and actions to store to the database.

Restlet is a framework on Java. Some of the steps to interact with Restlet include concepts related to web browsers, REST architecture, virtual hosts, static files, and URI redirection. In particular, this RESTlet framework contains diverse features that could be useful to create, scale, and extend API development projects. Restlet provides Web API support with REST and HTTP concepts, tunneling service with any HTTP methods, and automatic processes with URI variables extraction. Configuration includes Java via RESTlet API and via XML/WADL files. To scale a project, the service supports non-blocking NIO modes, asynchronous request processing decoupled from IO operations, and fully multi-threaded design per-request resource.

SproutCore is an open source framework on JavaScript. The origins of SproutCore go back to 2007, when the project was developed by Apple, inspired by Cocoa, and maintained by a growing community. This framework offers features to develop applications for web and mobile. Some of them include KVO, optimized view layer, 50,000 items with the same DOM, compliant with WAI-ARIA, and offline support via Apache and Cordova.

Datumbox Machine Learning Framework is written Java, which enables the development of Machine Learning and Statistical applications. With this framework, developers have access to a number of machine learning algorithms & statistical tests.

Cake PHP is a framework that aims to build web applications with less code. Simplicity and easiness are the core values for this framework. In the site users can review the reasons why Cake PHP is convenient to create web applications. Some of the rationale includes quick development, clean MVC conventions, and a friendly MIT license. Clinic Finder, MapMe, and ScratchMIT are 3 examples that currently deploy the Cake PHP framework.

Guzzle is a framework on PHP HTTP that allows to interact with web services. Guzzle's characteristics aim to simplify POST requests with pluggable HTTP handlers and synchronous/asynchronous requests. Components contain log, OAuth, cache, retry, and message integrity subscribers.
Flight is a micro-framework on PHP that allows developers to create RESTful applications. Flight requires PHP 5.3 or greater and it is licensed by MIT.

Fat-Free is a framework on PHP. To develop applications, users can refer to the guide available on the site, that includes instructions for interact with routing engines, plug-ins, and framework variables.

Sencha Touch is an HTML5 framework that helps to create mobile applications targeted to businesses. This framework provides over 50 built-in components, customized themes, and a built model view controller.

Atoms Neurospeech is a JavaScript framework inspired from Flex and Silverlight. Atoms offers one time/one way/two way bindings, component object model, one liner AJAX, customizable UI scopes, cascade selections, and ready to use line of business controls.

Rico is a framework on JavaScript that aims to ease interactive web application development. Drag-and-drop, HTML elements, and animation effects are some of the functions supported by this framework. Additionally, Rico offers grids that can be populated either with static content or dynamic content with AJAX. Translations to French, German, Italian, Portuguese, Spanish, Chinese, Japanese, Korean, Russian, and Ukrainian are available.
Prototype is an object-oriented framework on Javascript. It aims to facilitate web applications using class-style OO framework, Ajax support, and DOM manipulation.

Sencha Ext is a framework on Javascript that can be used to build business mobile applications. Version 5 offers additional features such as tablet support, grid widgets, model-view architecture, 2 way data binding, routing, and session management.

Dojo toolkit 1.10 is an HTML5 framework on Javascript for mobile application development. This framework allows developers to create apps in iOS 5+, Android 2.2+, Windows Phone 8+, Blackberry 6+, and Node.js 0.6 11+, 0.8 6+, and 0.10+.

Chaplin is a framework on Javascript that uses the Backbone.js library. With Chaplin, web application development should be easier due to the functionality, scalability, and accessibility offered on the site.
Sammy is a framework on Javascript. It is 16K compressed and 5.2 compressed and gzipped. This framework is built on plugins and adapters. It aims to extract developers' code into reusable plugins.

Can is a framework on Javascript. It aims to build applications that are flexible, powerful, and fast. It's flexible because developers can reuse templates. It's powerful because the framework contains 2 RESTful models. And it's fast because the responsive widgets can be learned in a day.
Backbone is a framework on Javascript. It connects events, collections, and functions to existent APIs over a RESTful JSON interface.

Written in Java and Android compatible, Licas allows you to build service-based networks. All of the main SOA features are included for distributed communications or architecture and additional packages allow for AI programming. Build lightweight networks of service-based components (SOA or Cloud). Programmable framework with many features - add/run services, add/search metadata, autonomous, agent-based, self-organizing and distributed communication. Java J2SE (1.5+) compatible. Communication includes XML-RPC, REST, HTTP and dynamic Web Services (SOAP). An 'All-in-One' GUI is a free tool, available from the DCS site and can be used to run all of the packages and separate modules. Alternatively, write programs using the stand-alone server, or by extending the open source classes. A p2p network can be setup requiring only the HTTP address and optional passwords. Example Apps are messenger, file sharing, web services, query. The code can also be used for more scientific programs. Sub-packages include text or query processing, or heuristic evaluation. A problem solver provides genetic algorithms and other AI algorithms, integrated into the whole system.
PyGtalkRobot is a Google Talk bot framework written in Python. This framework requires the user to have either Python 2.4+ or ActivePython. Its dependencies are xmpppy and pydns.
Derby.js is a framework designed for developers to create collaborative real time web applications. The MVC framework facilitates the creation of applications that serve in Node.js and the browser.

The Zendesk framework can be utilized to construct robust Zendesk-themed apps with the help of JavaScript APIs. Zendesk apps can enhance functionality such as ticket information, customer details, and time tracking.

Connect IQ a platform for third-party developers to create apps for Garmin products, and the Connect IQ SDK gives developers the tools to build these apps. With Connect IQ developers can customize the user experience with new faces, use the sensors to accumulate data and metrics, create widgets for instant information tidbits, and create fitness-reflated lifestyle web apps. A preview of the SDK is now available to start building apps for Garmin wearable devices. Devices that are compatible with Connect IQ will be available early 2015, but until then, the simulator included in the SDK will provide a testing platform for what is being built.

This Ruby on Rails gem allows developers to easily integrate Algolia into object relational mapping systems. The Algolia Search API can be implemented into web applications to reference a database to display a drop down of real time search results. The API supports quick faceted, full-text, and numerical search results.

Feed.Fm offers Unity SDK, a kit that wraps the REST API for the Unity environment. Developers can find a sample scene in the website to become aware of the functionality. In this case, the quickest way to understand how the kit works is to install the package and open the sample in Assets/FeedFm Demos/PlayerScene.unity. Additional to a sample scene, users can find guides related to the Player GUI that includes initialization, rendering, and caveats.

The Splunk developer platform consists of three primary components: Splunkd, the engine; Splunk Web, the app framework that sits on top of the engine; and the Splunk SDKs that interface with the REST API and extension points.The Splunk SDK for PHP lets developers target Splunkd by making calls against the engine's REST API and accessing the various Splunkd end points such as custom search commands, lookup functions, scripted inputs, and custom REST handlers.

GuildWars2::API is a PERL library that provides a set of standard interfaces for interacting with the Guild Wars 2 API. This library was written in PERL 5.16.3, and users will need to have at least PERL 5.14.0.

GW2API by Frugghi is an Objective-C framework for accessing the Guild Wars 2 API, especially for integration with iOS and OS X applications. The framework's prerequisites are OS X, iOS: 6.0+, and ARC.
Durmand Priory is a framework written in Objective-C for accessing the Guild Wars 2 API. All of the API's endpoints are included in the framework, but it's still a work in progress.

React is a JavaScript framework that helps developers build user interfaces. It can easily serve as the "view" element in a model-view-controller (MVC) stack since it makes no assumptions about the rest of the stack. The library is declarative, lightweight, efficient, and flexible.

Ember-Runtime is a framework that provides core functions for Ember including cross-platform functions, and support for property observing and objects. It's focus is on small size and performance. It is intended to be used in place of or along-side other cross-platform libraries such as jQuery. The core Runtime framework is based on the jQuery API with a number of performance optimizations.

Google provides AngularJS, a framework that can help developers to extend an application in HTML using Javascript objects. The site displays code with examples named basic html code, add some control, wire up backend, and create components. Such samples add js and css to the html to include style and functionality. In the main sites, users can view code on Githib and access the download file. To build an application using Angular, developers can practice in a browser at no cost.

Meteor is a service that allows users to build web applications. Some features of Meteor include application interoperability, data synchronization, and live page updates. The Meteor JavaScript Framework is an open source tool for developers to construct web apps purely using JavaScript.

Bottle is a Python Web Framework. With Bottle users can request calls, receive support for mako, jinja2 and cheetah templates. They can also access services to create data, upload files, cookies and headers. Bottle is built in HTTP and is supported with Google App Engine and WSGI servers.

Tornado is a framework developed at FriendFeed, a feed created with friends' news, articles, photos and videos and shared in multiple collaborative sites. With Tornado, users can access applications, websockets, and long polling code. This service is optimum for consumers who require lasting connections. The framework serves also as an asynchronous networking library.

Giotto is a framework based on the model, view and controllers (MVC) concept. Some of the characteristics of Giotto include a free RESTful interface, automatic URL routing, and Jinja2 for HTML templates with an API. This framework promotes functionality while the code for model, view, and controller is separated from an existing association.

The Nav SDK by Cloudmade is designed for developers to implement customizable tools into mobile devices for use in automobile navigation. Developed from the ground up, the Nav SDK supports multiple software platforms, compatible with Linux, QNX, Android, iOS, WinCE, and Windows Phone. The SDK is flexible enough to be implemented into various hardware platforms such as wearables, smartphone, and a car's dashboard control panel. Integrating 3rd party APIs for data sources is possible, and the SDK comes compatible with all major map providers. Some main features this hybrid offline/online SDK specializes in is route calculating, re-routing, voice control, and displaying traffic data.

easyXDM is a JavaScript framework that enables easy cross-domain messaging and JavaScript API exposure. It is a nearly independent framework written with light and flexible code. The framework allows the ability to transfer strings between two windows, termed a 'provider' and a 'consumer.' easyXDM works well with low latency on the following browsers: IE, Opera, Firefox, Safari, and Chrome.

Grape is a RESTful micro-framework that allows developers to build simple APIs in Ruby. With built in support for conventions and versioning, it's simplicity makes it an alternative to using a large framework such as Rails. Grape is designed with DSL to compliment existing web applications with an easy to implement API.
Zillow API in Cake allows developers to access the Zillow API using the CakePHP development framework. This framework is designed to help PHP users of all skill levels quickly develop applications.

restify is a small framework that borrows from express, used to build RESTful web services in Node.js. It provides out of the box support for features used to build such services such as versioning, error handling, content negotiation and CORS.
Express is a minimal node.js web application framework. It offers developers a full set of features for building single, multi-page, and hybrid web applications. Express is styled after Sinatra.

Hapi is a server framework for Node.js originally created by Walmart Labs. It is designed as a scalable web framework that can help developers evolve their system over time. Hapi offers REST API support and infrastructure for building web apps or serving static content.

FMEngine is an Objective-C framework created for the Last.fm API. The framework doesn't parse output from the Last.fm API, so users will need to use their own parsers. FMEngine can be used in iPhone and Mac OS X applications and is released under the MIT License.
lastfm-sharp is an open-source .NET interface to the Last.fm API. It comes with proxy support and is fully compatible with the .Net Framework and Mono.

Flickraw is a Ruby library that provides an interface to the Flickr API. Data returned through the interface is presented in a simple and intuitive manner. Because the library's methods are fetched from Flickr when it loads, the library is always up-to-date.

The PRINTR3D PHP Wrapper is designed to allow developers to easily integrate their PHP web applications with the Printr REST API's 3D printing services. This wrapper is being actively developed and updated by PRINTR.

FlickrKit is a library written in iOS Objective-C to help developers access the Flickr API. It is currently used by the Galleryr Pro iPad app.The library requires iOS 6.0 or above and has not been tested with older iOS versions.

ObjectiveFlickr is a framework for implementing the Flickr API in Objective-C. ObjectiveFlickr was designed for use in Mac and iPhone applications, but since it was developed for iOS 2.0, it may require some updates to match the current iOS version.
The very first Hacklang framework. It takes the best of the language and bring it to your applications: safety, speed and verboseness.

The OpenBR project has produced a new language for image recognition used to express algorithms. Each word in the language corresponds to a plugin that performs a specific transformation on an image, allowing for highly decoupled development of the individual steps in an algorithm. The OpenBR 0.4.0 framework (Open Source Biometric Recognition) and related APIs apply complex algorithms to measure facial features and give access control using advanced biometrics. The C++ plugins include Face Recognition, Age Estimation, and Gender Estimation. OpenBR is written in a subset of C++ and is known to work with all popular modern C++ compilers. The project is actively maintained on Windows, Mac, and Linux, with ports to Android & iOS.
Node IMDB API is a Node.js interface to the Unofficial IMDB API. It provides developers with a non-scraping method for getting information from IMDB.

The DocuSign Mobile SDK for iOS allows developers to integrate Digital Transaction Management services and eSignature functionality into mobile apps. With the SDK, developers can implement functionality such as signing and completing document-based transactions as well as hosting in-person signing sessions from within a mobile app.

This .NET SDK provides easy access to the Google Data APIs. It supports services like YouTube, Google Calendar, and Contacts. The Google Data APIs use the AtomPub protocol to read and write data to Google Services. Services supported include Google Calendar, Contacts, YouTube and more. This is a reference to a Google Code project.

Famo.us is an open source JavaScript framework for mobile applications. The best known feature of Famo.us is its rendering engine and 3D physics engine that can render to DOM, Canvas or WebGL. Developers can take advantage of the rendering and physics engine to build native speed apps and games in HTML5. Famo.us runs on iOS, Android, Kindle and Firefox devices and integrates with Angular, Backbone, Meteor and Facebook React.
Crafted.Twitter is compromised of an ASP .Net web form and MVC HTMLhelper extension to help developers implement tweets on their website.

Zend Framework 2 is an open source object oriented framework for developing web applications in PHP 5. Zend Framework uses many of the new features of PHP 5.3, including namespaces, late static binding, lambda functions and closures.
Spring Application Framework provides connection support and API binding for Twitter.
Simple ASP code library supporting the Twitter API v 1.1
The Twitter iOS framework provides developers with framework examples for iOS5+ and iOS6+

FRAPI is an API Open Source RESTful API Framework consisting of two specific parts: The administration interface and the public API. It is designed to let developers focus on business logic and not the frontend presentation layer.

Recess is a RESTful, full-stack PHP framework designed to support both experienced and beginning developers. Its small footprint makes it a good choice for LAMP development. Recess is designed for PHP 5 and uses a loosely coupled Model-View Controller.
Tonic is an open-source RESTful web App PHP micro-framework. Features include URI annotations, support for content and language negotiation, method conditions and mount points.
Epiphany is a micro PHP framework meant to be clean and RESTful. It is designed to be simple yet powerful.

Slim is a lightweight micro framework that developers can use to build web applications and RESTful APIs in PHP. Features include a router, a resource locator and DI container, template rendering with custom views and more.
Includes Spring Social's core service provider connect framework and web support.

The 140dev Twitter Framework is a free source code library containing a Twitter database server for gathering tweets for selected keywords, as well as a display plugin that lets you show tweets from the database in a single line of PHP code.
Zend Framework based client for the Twilio API. Still in the first stages of development. Expect things to change. The example code should remain relatively stable, but there are no guarantees.
An overview and introduction to an open source project, Facebook.NET, a framework optimized for developing ASP.NET-based Facebook applications.
